# JavaScript Functions Overview

```javascript
// Function Declaration
function sum(a, b) {
    return a + b;
}

// Function Expression
const multiply = function(x, y) {
    return x * y;
};

// Arrow Function
const divide = (dividend, divisor) => dividend / divisor;

// Usage
console.log(sum(5, 3)); // Output: 8
console.log(multiply(4, 2)); // Output: 8
console.log(divide(10, 2)); // Output: 5
```

### Function Types:

| Type             | Description                          |
|------------------|--------------------------------------|
| Declaration      | Named functions with hoisting benefits |
| Expression       | Anonymous functions stored in variables |
| Arrow            | Compact syntax with context binding  |

# JavaScript Function Control Flow

```mermaid
flowchart TD
    Start(Start) --> CheckInput{Is Input Valid?}
    CheckInput -->|Yes| ProcessData[Process Data]
    CheckInput -->|No| HandleError[Handle Error]
    ProcessData --> SaveResults[Save Results]
    SaveResults --> End(End)
    HandleError --> End
```

### Example Code:

```javascript
function processInput(input) {
    if (typeof input !== 'string') {
        console.error('Invalid input!');
        return;
    }
    const processed = input.trim().toUpperCase();
    console.log(processed);
}

// Test
processInput(' Hello World '); // Output: 'HELLO WORLD'
processInput(123); // Output: 'Invalid input!'
```

> **Note:** Effective use of control flow enhances error handling and data processing in functions.
